Continental Airlines sets warrant purchase . Continental Airlines said on Thursday that Air Partners LP exercised its previously announced right to sell to Continental $ 50 million of warrants to purchase Class B common stock issued earlier by Continental . The $ 50 million is in intrinsic value , which is the current Class B common stock price minus the exercise price . As a result , Continental said it will purchase , for $ 50 million in cash , warrants to buy 2 , 614 , 379 Class B shares at an exercise price of $ 7 . 50 per share . The transaction will close early next week . Air Partners continues to be the company ' s largest stockholder , Continental said . 
